.SH NAME
\fBfindll(1f) \fP- [FILE FILTER] find long lines
\fB(LICENSE:PD)
.SH SYNOPSIS
.nf
.fam C
\fBfindll\fP [ \fB-l\fP \fILENGTH\fP] [ \fB-wrap\fP] | [ \fB-help\fP| \fB-version\fP] [FILENAMES]
.fam T
.fi
.SH DESCRIPTION
find lines in files over a specified length and print
them; or wrap each input line to fit in specified width.
.PP
Lines ending in a backslash ("\\") are concatenated with the
next line.
.PP
Non-printable characters are not treated specially (eg. a
tab character is treated as a single character).
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.B \fIFILENAMES\fP
the files to scan for long lines
.TP
.B \fB-l\fP NUMBER
maximum line length of lines to ignore.
The default is 132.
.TP
.B \fB--wrap\fP
instead of locating and displaying long
lines, fold the lines at the specified
line length
.TP
.B \fB--help\fP
display this help and exit
.TP
.B \fB--version\fP
output version information and exit
.SH EXAMPLES
Sample commands:
.PP
.nf
.fam C
   $ findll <filename

   # show lines over 72 characters in length
   $ findll *.f *.F -l 72
   # show length of all lines on stdin
   $ findll -l -1

.fam T
.fi
